latestPosts.caption:
never thought i’d actually do this but… i went scuba diving for the first time ever in bali 🐠completely solo, with a bunch of strangers, in another country, and somehow, it turned out to be one of the best days of my life 🫶

i was so nervous and lowkey freaking out while putting on the gear 😅 kept thinking “what if i panic underwater? what if i can’t breathe?” 

but the moment i took that first breath and went under… everything just shifted. it was calm. quiet. weirdly peaceful. like the world above didn’t exist for a bit.

i don’t even know how to explain it properly but it felt like something inside me clicked- like i did something brave just for me and came out of it feeling proud, happy, and honestly… kinda emotional?? 🥹

still thinking about it. still smiling about it. definitely one for the books 💙
.
.
.
